Express Application Functions (Complete Reference)
What is an Express Application?

An Express Application is an object returned by the express() function.

const express = require('express');
const app = express();


The app object contains application functions used to:

Handle routes

Configure settings

Add middleware

Start the server

1. app.listen()
Purpose

Starts the Express server and listens for incoming requests.

Syntax
app.listen(port, callback);

Example
app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server started on port 3000');
});

2. app.get()
Purpose

Handles GET HTTP requests.

Syntax
app.get(path, callback);

Example
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Home Page');
});

3. app.post()
Purpose

Handles POST HTTP requests.

Example
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Login Success');
});

4. app.put()
Purpose

Handles PUT requests (update entire data).

app.put('/user/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User Updated');
});

5. app.patch()
Purpose

Handles PATCH requests (partial update).

app.patch('/user/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User Partially Updated');
});

6. app.delete()
Purpose

Handles DELETE requests.

app.delete('/user/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User Deleted');
});

7. app.use()
Purpose

Registers middleware.

Syntax
app.use([path], middleware);

Example
app.use(express.json());
app.use('/api', userRoutes);

8. app.all()
Purpose

Handles all HTTP methods for a route.

app.all('/test', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Works for all methods');
});

9. app.route()
Purpose

Creates chainable route handlers.

Example
app.route('/student')
  .get((req, res) => res.send('Get Student'))
  .post((req, res) => res.send('Add Student'))
  .put((req, res) => res.send('Update Student'));

10. app.set()
Purpose

Sets application-level variables.

app.set('view engine', 'ejs');

11. app.get(setting)
Purpose

Gets application settings.

app.get('view engine');

12. app.engine()
Purpose

Registers a template engine.

app.engine('html', require('ejs').renderFile);

13. app.param()
Purpose

Runs logic when a route parameter is present.

app.param('id', (req, res, next, id) => {
  console.log(id);
  next();
});

14. app.disable()
Purpose

Disables application setting.

app.disable('x-powered-by');

15. app.enable()
Purpose

Enables application setting.

app.enable('trust proxy');

16. app.disabled()
Purpose

Checks if setting is disabled.

app.disabled('etag'); // true / false

17. app.enabled()
Purpose

Checks if setting is enabled.

app.enabled('trust proxy');

18. app.locals
Purpose

Stores global variables accessible in views.

app.locals.title = 'My App';

Common Express Application Flow
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Welcome');
});

app.listen(3000);
